article.headline: Hill-Thomas leads Nevada with 18
article.linkText: Hill-Thomas tips in game-winner for Nevada
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Garry Hill-Thomas scored a game-high 18 points and tipped in the winning basket as time expired Saturday night to keep Nevada undefeated at home this season with a 60-58 victory over Toledo. Kevinn Pinkey added 13 points and 12 rebounds and Kirk Snyder had 10 points for the Wolf Pack (17-8), who are 13-0 at home. Sammy Villegas tied the game at 58-58 on a 3-point shot with 7.5 seconds left for Toledo (16-8). Nevada's Todd Okeson took the ensuing inbounds pass and dribbled the length of the court before his shot in the lane bounced off the rim. Hill-Thomas tipped it in. The officials briefly reviewed a videotape before determining that the tip beat the buzzer. Hill-Thomas turned a steal into a slam dunk to put Nevada ahead 56-50 with 2:33 remaining. Villegas was credited with a basket inside when Snyder was called for goal-tending at 1:25 and Ingram nailed a 3-pointer with 36 seconds left to pull within 56-55. Okeson made two free throws for a 58-55 lead with 22 seconds on the clock before Villegas' 3-pointer made for the dramatic finish. Nevada held Toledo scoreless during a 6-minute stretch in the first half to help build a 36-26 halftime lead, and later went ahead 43-35 on Marcelus Kemp's 17-foot jump shot with 14:07 left. Villegas hit a 3-pointer and a 19-foot jumper to pull the Rockets to within 43-41 with 11 minutes remaining. But Snyder scored the next 5 points to put Nevada ahead 48-41 with 9:15 to play. Villegas finished with a team-high 14 points and eight rebounds for Toledo. Ingram scored 11. Keith Triplett, Toledo's leading scorer at 19.2 points per game, scored only 5 before he left the game just before the half with a broken nose. He did not return. The 13-0 mark is Nevada's best start at home since the school moved up to Division I before the 1969-70 season. The Wolf Pack are now 17-0 when leading at the half, 0-8 when trailing at halftime.
